  "text": "Li et al. [CITATION_1] provide an approach for image and video editing with instant results. They employ radial basis function interpolation in a feature space to propagate sparse edits locally. In contrast to this work, we are formulating the problem as a global color space transformation independent from the image space and we optimize the shape of basis functions to achieve color balancing behavior found in example images. We show that the basis function used by Li et al. is suboptimal for the purpose of global image balancing.",
